25:57.082 --> 25:59.850
Asleep in my room.

25:59.852 --> 26:01.718
Did anyone see you?

26:01.720 --> 26:03.820
I was asleep.

26:03.822 --> 26:05.422
RUTLEDGE: You had motive.

26:05.424 --> 26:07.724
You had opportunity.

26:07.726 --> 26:09.159
Isn't it possible

26:09.161 --> 26:12.562
you killed Alyssa?

26:14.666 --> 26:16.066
- (yells)
- (gasping)

26:16.068 --> 26:17.033
- Oh!
- (gavel banging)

26:17.035 --> 26:18.001
JUDGE: Quiet in the court!

26:18.003 --> 26:19.736
(gallery murmuring)

26:19.738 --> 26:22.239
Didn't see that coming.

26:25.411 --> 26:26.410
(handcuffs jingling)

26:26.412 --> 26:27.677
Taylor.

26:27.679 --> 26:29.846
MAN (over radio): Eagle coming
out of the courthouse.

26:29.848 --> 26:31.648
MAN 2 (over radio): Transpo
en route. 30 seconds out.

26:31.650 --> 26:32.716
MAN: Watch your six.

26:32.718 --> 26:34.084
The dead girl's father is approaching

26:34.086 --> 26:35.685
in a blue windbreaker.

26:35.687 --> 26:37.254
MAN 2: Eyes on target.
Eyes on the prize.

26:37.256 --> 26:38.455
Secure the perimeter.

26:39.024 --> 26:40.991
(gunshots)

26:40.993 --> 26:44.027
(panicked clamoring)

26:54.016 --> 26:56.409
But don't you see what
a break this is for us?

26:57.008 --> 26:59.369
Clyde wants to move for a mistrial.

26:59.371 --> 27:02.472
Well, this might be the
first time we get a fair trial.

27:02.474 --> 27:05.509
Now that Wyatt Earp has put
some points on the board,

27:05.511 --> 27:07.517
they can stop using your
son to stick it to you.

27:07.518 --> 27:09.379
The jury saw the whole thing.

27:09.381 --> 27:11.748
How is that not grounds for a mistrial?

27:11.750 --> 27:13.083
Well, he missed.

27:13.085 --> 27:15.852
Mostly.

27:15.854 --> 27:18.155
We have a hung jury,

27:18.157 --> 27:19.766
according to your data.

27:19.767 --> 27:20.979
Then we go again.

27:20.981 --> 27:22.447
A-Another trial?

27:22.449 --> 27:25.017
Half the time with a hung
jury, the D.A. drops it.

27:26.954 --> 27:28.720
What if he's guilty?

27:32.292 --> 27:33.492
What does Brandon say?

27:33.494 --> 27:36.962
Have you even spoken to your son?

27:36.964 --> 27:40.165
He'll do what I tell him to do.

27:40.167 --> 27:42.567
He always has.

27:43.604 --> 27:46.038
You basically told him he
wasn't worth your time

27:46.040 --> 27:49.541
and he has lived up to
those expectations.

27:53.580 --> 27:56.882
Tell me he didn't do this.

27:59.753 --> 28:02.487
(computers trilling, phones ringing)

28:02.489 --> 28:03.922
I just watched the mirror jury

28:03.924 --> 28:06.258
deliberate for two and a half hours.

28:06.260 --> 28:07.592
We're losing.

28:07.594 --> 28:09.227
I like a challenge.

28:09.229 --> 28:11.696
It's one of the ten traits
of highly successful people.

28:11.698 --> 28:13.698
Hmm.

28:16.470 --> 28:20.405
A victim wants a caretaker.

28:20.407 --> 28:22.774
These people...

28:22.776 --> 28:24.643
are all linked...

28:24.645 --> 28:26.078
to Bess.

28:26.080 --> 28:28.180
We still don't have her.

28:31.652 --> 28:32.984
Her son,

28:32.986 --> 28:37.122
AJ, went through life
looking for the father he never had.

28:39.827 --> 28:41.693
Just like Brandon

28:41.695 --> 28:45.831
went through life looking for
the father he never had.

28:45.833 --> 28:48.934
When Bess sees
Brandon, she sees her son, AJ.

28:48.936 --> 28:52.237
Bess's second chance to
save her son, through Brandon.

28:52.239 --> 28:53.705
Can I talk to you?

28:53.707 --> 28:55.607
Would you mind taking your earbuds out?

28:55.609 --> 28:58.410
"While employers believe
it's rude to wear earbuds

28:58.412 --> 29:00.345
in the workplace, millennials
are using them

29:00.347 --> 29:02.414
to focus and be more productive."

29:02.416 --> 29:03.915
It's in our HR manual.

29:03.917 --> 29:05.684
Too long, didn't read.

29:05.686 --> 29:08.286
Remember we put that
bug in Clyde's watch?

29:08.288 --> 29:10.322
He's meeting with the D.A.

29:10.324 --> 29:12.457
You don't have Singapore Ear, do you?

29:12.459 --> 29:15.427
He's taking a deal... Second
degree manslaughter.

29:15.429 --> 29:18.997
He's gonna plead Brandon guilty.

29:18.999 --> 29:21.433
I want Brandon downstairs.

29:21.435 --> 29:23.435
- (door opens)
- Hey.

29:23.437 --> 29:25.704
Don't mind him, I
borrowed him from the law firm.

29:25.706 --> 29:27.639
Earbuds, Josh.

29:27.641 --> 29:29.741
It just means whatever
we say in here is protected

29:29.743 --> 29:31.343
under attorney-client privilege.

29:31.345 --> 29:32.444
Why are we meeting down here?

29:32.446 --> 29:33.545
Take a seat.

29:33.547 --> 29:34.646
Why?

29:34.648 --> 29:36.114
Just have a seat.

29:36.116 --> 29:38.550
I'm not gonna testify.

29:38.552 --> 29:39.751
Do you like Nutraloaf?

29:39.753 --> 29:41.686
My father said I'm gonna take a deal.

29:41.688 --> 29:42.654
'Cause that's what you're
gonna be eating

29:42.656 --> 29:44.789
for the next ten years.

29:47.594 --> 29:49.194
Forget it.

29:49.196 --> 29:50.162
I'm not doing it.

29:50.164 --> 29:51.997
(scoffs) Now is not the time

29:51.999 --> 29:55.268
to bail on yourself just
because Daddy is.

29:56.069 --> 29:58.870
I know, Brandon. I've
been down that road.

29:58.872 --> 30:00.372
Yeah, right.

30:00.374 --> 30:03.608
I... I mean, everybody respects you.

30:03.610 --> 30:06.178
Even my dad says you're the best.

30:06.180 --> 30:08.680
Your dad...

30:15.856 --> 30:18.156
Dads...

30:20.961 --> 30:25.030
If a father never said, "I love you,"

30:25.032 --> 30:26.932
right?

30:26.934 --> 30:29.201
Never.

30:31.405 --> 30:33.972
Never said, "I'm proud of you."

30:35.976 --> 30:38.243
Couldn't say it.

30:41.348 --> 30:44.015
'Cause he didn't believe it.

30:44.017 --> 30:45.917
Then who's the failure?

30:45.919 --> 30:49.421
The father or the son?

30:52.893 --> 30:55.227
Look in the mirror

30:55.229 --> 30:58.663
and be the man your father never was.

30:58.665 --> 31:02.467
Give yourself what you
wish you could get

31:02.469 --> 31:05.270
from somebody else.

31:06.139 --> 31:09.207
I'll be right there with you.

31:11.445 --> 31:14.212
(sighs)

31:14.214 --> 31:17.616
Sometimes I feel like
this whole thing...

31:17.618 --> 31:20.085
you know, like...

31:20.087 --> 31:22.954
like I'm watching it
happen to somebody else.

31:26.360 --> 31:28.460
I know you're gay, Brandon.

31:29.296 --> 31:31.863
I've known for a long time.

31:31.865 --> 31:33.331
And it's nothing to be ashamed of.

31:33.333 --> 31:36.167
(chuckles) It's who you are.

31:37.037 --> 31:39.904
(exhales deeply)

31:39.906 --> 31:41.439
How did you know?

31:42.876 --> 31:44.409
I didn't even know.

31:44.411 --> 31:47.412
Isn't that where you were the
night Alyssa was murdered?

31:47.414 --> 31:51.750
Somewhere else,
with someone else, doing...

31:52.586 --> 31:54.286
...something else?

31:58.392 --> 31:59.891
Does my father know?

31:59.893 --> 32:02.260
Your father just made a deal

32:02.262 --> 32:03.928
to put you in prison for ten years.

32:03.930 --> 32:05.297
Did he even ask you?

32:15.942 --> 32:18.476
(breathes shakily)

32:25.285 --> 32:28.486
(sniffles)

32:30.557 --> 32:32.424
You can do this.

32:33.627 --> 32:35.894
(nervous sigh)

32:38.799 --> 32:40.632
They're not going to believe me.

32:40.634 --> 32:42.801
Hey...

32:42.803 --> 32:45.203
don't give up on people.

32:45.205 --> 32:47.405
They're all we've got.

32:49.910 --> 32:51.976
- Speak up.
- Answer directly.

32:51.978 --> 32:53.078
Keep your hands still.

32:53.080 --> 32:54.012
BENNY: Don't slouch.

32:54.014 --> 32:55.080
MARISSA: Respond only to questions,

32:55.082 --> 32:56.214
not statements.

32:56.216 --> 32:59.017
- Don't fill silences.
- Don't smoke on breaks.

32:59.019 --> 33:00.385
It's not enough to tell the truth.

33:00.387 --> 33:01.787
You have to tell the truth effectively.

33:01.788 --> 33:04.089
I gotta get this to my
boss. He'll need time to prepare.

33:04.091 --> 33:05.757
Clyde's not doing the direct, you are.

33:05.759 --> 33:07.225
(Benny chokes, coughs)

33:07.227 --> 33:09.027
What? Does he know that?

33:09.029 --> 33:11.863
(scoffs) My read on the
women on this jury is

33:11.865 --> 33:13.898
they hate your boss.

33:13.900 --> 33:15.767
If we spring you on them,

33:15.769 --> 33:18.970
they just may rally to
vote for you, Liberty,

33:18.972 --> 33:21.005
rather than against Brandon.

33:24.444 --> 33:26.878
I'm the client, right? I'll tell him.

33:42.037 --> 33:44.238
LIBERTY: Brandon...

33:45.041 --> 33:46.841
I want you to direct your attention

33:46.843 --> 33:48.643
to the night in question.

33:49.512 --> 33:51.846
Were you with Alyssa Yang that night?

33:51.848 --> 33:53.347
Yes, I was.

33:53.349 --> 33:56.550
And on a previous night,
did you have sex with her?

33:56.552 --> 33:58.552
Yes.

33:58.554 --> 34:00.721
Did you argue about sex?

34:02.458 --> 34:04.291
I didn't want to have
sex with her again.

34:04.293 --> 34:06.093
It was a mistake.

34:06.095 --> 34:07.328
Did something go wrong?

34:07.330 --> 34:09.230
It's a mistake to do everything in life

34:09.232 --> 34:11.465
because of what other
people expect you to.

34:11.467 --> 34:13.534
LIBERTY: You're a healthy young man.

34:13.536 --> 34:15.670
She was a beautiful young girl.

34:15.672 --> 34:17.705
Why not?

34:17.706 --> 34:19.440
Well, my parents kept asking me why

34:19.442 --> 34:20.675
I didn't have a girlfriend,

34:20.677 --> 34:23.444
and Alyssa was one of the
hottest girls around

34:23.446 --> 34:25.980
and an "A" student who could, you know,

34:25.982 --> 34:27.380
go to Oxford.

34:27.382 --> 34:30.518
So that was, like, a
perfect picture, and...

34:30.520 --> 34:33.654
at a certain point you get tired

34:33.656 --> 34:36.257
of disappointing everyone.

34:38.094 --> 34:40.960
So what was wrong with
the perfect picture?

34:46.402 --> 34:47.935
I'm gay.

34:49.205 --> 34:51.205
(quiet murmuring)

34:52.308 --> 34:54.608
Is that where you were
between 1:00 a.m. and 3:00 a.m.?

34:56.879 --> 34:58.612
Yes.

34:58.614 --> 35:00.081
I was with someone.

35:00.883 --> 35:03.217
LIBERTY: Brandon, I have to ask you...

35:04.220 --> 35:06.353
...who were you with?

35:06.355 --> 35:10.091
Look, I mean no
disrespect to you or anyone,

35:10.093 --> 35:12.026
but I'm not gonna answer that.

35:12.028 --> 35:15.329
I said what I've
said, and I'm not sorry,

35:15.331 --> 35:17.565
but I'm not gonna do
this to someone else.

35:17.567 --> 35:20.901
Brandon, now is not the
time to be a hero.

35:20.903 --> 35:22.870
I've told you
everything you need to know.

35:24.574 --> 35:27.041
Brandon, did you kill Alyssa Yang?

35:27.043 --> 35:29.844
- No.
- Save yourself.

35:29.846 --> 35:32.246
Tell this jury who you were with.

35:32.248 --> 35:34.849
You just want...

35:34.851 --> 35:36.517
You want to break it all apart.

35:36.519 --> 35:38.786
Break everything!

35:38.788 --> 35:41.222
(shouting) You're
supposed to be the adults!

35:41.224 --> 35:43.624
(whispering and murmuring)

35:43.626 --> 35:45.760
(gavel banging)

35:45.762 --> 35:47.895
JUDGE: Quiet, please!

35:49.866 --> 35:51.766
(gavel banging)

35:54.771 --> 35:58.472
We have no further questions, Your Honor.

36:00.009 --> 36:01.442
So you didn't tell the police

36:01.444 --> 36:02.710
you were with someone that night?

36:02.712 --> 36:04.678
- No.
- You lied to the police.

36:04.680 --> 36:06.947
- Objection.
- I'll withdraw the question.

36:07.950 --> 36:10.451
You admit you had sex with Alyssa.

36:10.453 --> 36:13.287
Your DNA was found in her body.

36:13.289 --> 36:15.523
- You were never gay before...
- I was always gay! I...

36:15.525 --> 36:17.691
And now that your
trial isn't going so well...

36:17.693 --> 36:20.561
do you really
expect this jury to believe

36:20.563 --> 36:22.797
that you were with a secret,
gay, mystery lover

36:22.799 --> 36:24.298
who you refuse to name?

36:25.568 --> 36:28.536
I just didn't think it was
really up to me to be happy.

36:28.538 --> 36:29.770
Your refusal is answer enough.

36:29.772 --> 36:31.105
I'll withdraw the question.

36:31.107 --> 36:33.174
No further questions.

36:40.183 --> 36:42.116
- How did I do?
- Well...

36:42.118 --> 36:43.984
you're not done yet.

36:45.254 --> 36:47.321
I'm doing the closing argument, too?

36:47.323 --> 36:49.523
Well, the real
closing arguments take place

36:49.525 --> 36:51.258
behind the jury room door.

36:51.260 --> 36:52.593
Always.

36:53.896 --> 36:57.431
And our research shows that
Bess will deliver it.

36:58.467 --> 37:03.103
Bess... who carries a
terrible burden of guilt

37:03.105 --> 37:06.073
for failing her own son.

37:06.075 --> 37:08.442
You can free her from that.

37:09.312 --> 37:11.178
Can you do it?

37:20.990 --> 37:24.558
Brandon Peters did not kill Alyssa Yang.

37:25.628 --> 37:28.662
People know the truth when they hear it.

37:28.664 --> 37:31.532
That's why we say it has a ring.

37:33.236 --> 37:35.369
To tell the world that you're gay...

37:35.371 --> 37:37.438
to tell yourself...

37:37.440 --> 37:41.075
is not something you
do out of convenience.

37:42.245 --> 37:46.647
It might be the hardest conversation
you ever have.

37:46.649 --> 37:48.515
In not giving us an alibi

37:48.517 --> 37:51.085
he gave us, perhaps, the best alibi

37:51.087 --> 37:53.287
we could ever want.

37:53.289 --> 37:57.758
It's an old-fashioned word
you don't hear so much of anymore,

37:57.760 --> 38:00.561
you don't see so much of anymore.

38:01.898 --> 38:03.964
Character.

38:11.040 --> 38:12.506
(gavel banging)

38:23.719 --> 38:26.086
Would the foreman read the verdict?

38:32.395 --> 38:35.429
FOREMAN: On the charge of
murder in the second degree...

38:37.199 --> 38:39.266
...we find the defendant...

38:39.268 --> 38:41.368
not guilty.

38:41.370 --> 38:43.404
(excited murmurs)

38:43.406 --> 38:45.506
JUDGE: Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

38:45.508 --> 38:46.707
thank you for your service

38:46.709 --> 38:50.945
and for being an integral
part in the judicial process.

38:50.947 --> 38:52.379
You are dismissed.

38:52.381 --> 38:54.081
(gavel bangs)

39:14.437 --> 39:16.704
Good work, Brandon.

39:37.626 --> 39:38.692
ADELE: Let's go, Taylor.

39:38.694 --> 39:40.327
TAYLOR: Where are we going now?

39:40.329 --> 39:41.695
ADELE: Taylor, let's go.

39:41.697 --> 39:43.564
Meet with your therapist.

39:43.566 --> 39:44.732
TAYLOR: What?

39:44.734 --> 39:47.401
Mom, it's not for an hour.

39:58.314 --> 40:01.849
Excuse me. Bess. Hey.

40:01.851 --> 40:04.451
Oh, I recognize you.

40:04.453 --> 40:06.020
You were always watching us.

40:06.022 --> 40:08.022
(chuckles)

40:08.024 --> 40:09.723
I'm Dr. Jason Bull.

40:09.725 --> 40:11.792
What kind of doctor are you?

40:11.794 --> 40:13.460
Psychologist.

40:14.296 --> 40:17.531
Is that what you do, analyze people?

40:17.533 --> 40:20.401
Not like that. Different.

40:20.403 --> 40:22.903
Well, I was watching you, too.

40:22.905 --> 40:25.205
Oh, yeah?

40:27.410 --> 40:29.443
You grew up with a
lot of pain, didn't you?

40:31.013 --> 40:33.947
That's how you learn how
to watch people like that.

40:33.949 --> 40:36.350
Read 'em.

40:36.352 --> 40:38.719
Figure out what makes 'em go.

40:40.156 --> 40:43.190
To survive in that home. Mm.

40:43.192 --> 40:44.992
I know.

40:44.994 --> 40:46.994
I know.

40:47.863 --> 40:49.029
Can I ask you a question?

40:49.031 --> 40:50.431
Look, can we walk while we talk?

40:50.433 --> 40:51.698
I don't like getting home after dark.

40:51.700 --> 40:53.967
- Why'd you vote not guilty?
- Stop!

40:54.737 --> 40:57.204
Stop trying to figure people out,

40:57.206 --> 40:59.239
just to get 'em to do what you want.

41:01.844 --> 41:03.977
It's just a very lonely place.

41:06.916 --> 41:09.349
I wish I could.

41:11.220 --> 41:14.154
I've never seen so many lost children.

41:16.992 --> 41:19.960
What did we do?

41:22.765 --> 41:25.199
Why do you catch a cold?

41:37.880 --> 41:40.848
ADELE: I just don't know how you
could have been so reckless.

41:40.850 --> 41:42.449
And with Brandon!

41:43.853 --> 41:45.752
These things happen.

41:45.754 --> 41:48.322
Well, it's not gonna happen again.

41:51.694 --> 41:53.594
Good night.

41:55.297 --> 41:57.664
(door opens, closes)

42:25.261 --> 42:28.529
